### Delete-files preview detailed context
- Current behavior: `Clear Cancelled -> Delete files too` only shows totals after delete (count of files/logs), not exact file names.
- Required UX: before deleting, show a confirm dialog listing each cancelled task and the exact files that will be removed.
- Include per task:
	- Parent filename target(s): `filename`, `filename.part`, `filename.ytdl`
	- Playlist child item targets with same suffix handling
	- Log file path (if present)
- Show per-file status in preview when possible:
	- Exists (will delete)
	- Missing (already gone)
- Confirm actions:
	- `Cancel`
	- `Queue only` (no file deletion)
	- `Delete listed files`
- Post-action summary:
	- Number of cancelled tasks cleared
	- Number of files deleted
	- Number of logs deleted
	- Number of delete failures (if any)

### Process lifecycle detailed context (cancel + completion)
- Current requirement: when user cancels, downloader process must be killed immediately to avoid lag from lingering instances.
- Must apply to both:
	- Single video downloads
	- Playlist downloads
- Must also guarantee cleanup after natural finish/error:
	- No lingering `yt-dlp` or child process remains after completion
	- No lingering `ffmpeg` child process remains
- Expected behavior:
	- Cancel action: immediate process-tree termination (`/T /F` on Windows equivalent behavior)
	- Complete/error action: explicit final cleanup of process handle/tree
	- UI state should move to cancelled/done/error without delayed stale updates
- Verification checklist:
	- Repeated start/cancel cycles do not increase active background process count
	- Completing multiple playlist items leaves no residual downloader instances
	- App remains responsive while canceling active tasks

## Single-video support notes
- Reuse the existing yt-dlp process flow in `lib/data/datasources/process/ytdlp_datasource.dart`.
- Keep `DownloadTask` metadata updates working for title, channel, thumbnail, progress, and filename.
- Make sure the downloader UI treats a single video as one task, not a playlist container.
- Keep history entries populated for single videos with channel and thumbnail.

## YouTube smart downloader should have
- Smart format selection for video/audio based on quality and device needs.
- Single-video and playlist support with clear UI paths.
- Resume, retry, and cancellation controls per task.
- Metadata capture for title, channel, thumbnail, duration, and filesize.
- Subtitle, chapter, and metadata embedding options.
- Download presets for fast, balanced, and high-quality modes.
- Per-task output folder selection and filename templating.
- Post-processing hooks for merge, audio extract, and cleanup.
- Better failure handling with actionable error messages.
- History, search, and filters for completed downloads.

## Professional downloader UI actions checklist

